History
n the original article, feiffer described a syndrome with skull and limb anomalies in eight persons from a three-generation family [1]. ince then, several reports have documented its high clinical variability and genetic heterogeneity.History
In the original article, Pfeiffer described a syndrome with skull and limb anomalies in eight persons from a three-generation family [1]. Since then, several reports have documented its high clinical variability and genetic heterogeneity.
