β€ ype 2 consists of trilobated skull deformity (cloverleaf skull), extreme proptosis, finger and toes abnormalities, elbow ankylosis or synostosis, developmental delay and neurological complications. he cloverleaf skull can cause limited brain growth, and the extreme proptosis can cause severe visual impairments.
